Program: Outlook
Title: Driving a Red Cross Ambulance in The Lebanon
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbsgr
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Talking to the Lebanese Red Cross ambulance driver whose ambulance was hit by a missile. Also, an interview with American film director and insomniac Alan Berliner. Kent Aldrich on defying his lung cancer with a walk across Switzerland. Stories of women at a refuge for battered women in Egypt.